						<summary>

						<p>Slab kept near the Basavaṇṇa temple.</p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II [A.D. 1149].</p>						

						<p>This mutilated inscription refers to 10th regnal year of Jagadēkamalla, Prabhava.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land by Nāgiseṭṭi and others to a Jaina deity. Mentions Āchaladēvi and the Kadamba chief Taila-maṇḍalēsa.</p>						

						</summary>
